.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE COOKIES-PB D "30 Jun 86" 1986
.RZ "AMAZING COOKIES" "Simple peanut-butter cookies"
These are very simple peanut-butter cookies.  They turn out a
little moist, but are yummy.
.IH "Makes 1 batch"
.IG "1 cup" "peanut-butter" "180 g"
.IG "1 cup" "sugar" "190 g"
.IG "1" "large egg"
.PH
.SK 1
Beat the egg.  Don't let your neighbours find out, though.
.SK 2
Mix everything together.
.SK 3
Preheat oven to 
.TE 325 160 .
.SK 4
Place blobs of cookie dough on a greased cookie sheet in the size you like,
and flatten with a fork to make the traditional peanut-butter cookie pattern.
.SK 5
Put in oven and bake for 8\-10 minutes.
.NX
These cookies are a bit moist, so don't worry about that.  Don't burn them;
they don't taste good when they're burnt.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
5 minutes preparation, 10 minutes baking.
.I Precision:
Measure the ingredients.
.WR
Andrew Scott Beals
Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory, Computation Research Group
Livermore, California, U.S.A.
